R Notebook

Load http request / duration data exported from prometheus monitoring a few gitblit instances. The data was artificially created on my pc.

library(readr)
http_requests_duration_per_second <- read_csv("~/Dropbox/AnomaliesDetector/anomd/data/experiment_1/http_requests_duration_per_second.csv",  col_types = cols(datetime = col_datetime(format = "%m/%d/%Y %H:%M")))

Normalize data, to a format usable for the creation of a linear model.

http_requests_second <- read_csv("~/Dropbox/AnomaliesDetector/anomd/data/experiment_1/http_requests_per_second.csv",  col_types = cols(datetime = col_datetime(format = "%m/%d/%Y %H:%M")))
http_requests_duration_per_second$date.numeric = as.numeric(http_requests_duration_per_second$datetime)/(24*60*60)
http_requests_second$date.numeric = as.numeric(http_requests_second$datetime)/(24*60*60)
requests_data = merge(http_requests_duration_per_second[c('GET', 'date.numeric')], 
                      http_requests_second[c('GET', 'date.numeric')], 
                      by = 'date.numeric',
                      suffixes = c(".duration",".requests"))

Calculate linear regression, request duration dependent on time, model similar to Prometheus predict_linear & Visualize the model efficiency

lm_model_1 = lm(GET.duration ~  date.numeric , data = requests_data)
summary(lm_model_1)

Calculate linear regression, request duration dependent on number of requests. To my knowledge this is not possible in prometheus yet.

lm_model_2 = lm(GET.requests ~ GET.duration, data = requests_data)
